The paper deals with the problem of coordination between two agents over a noisy communication channel, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and game theory (cs.GT) concepts. The proposed schemes also involve artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques for generating action sequences. The problem of coordination is relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) applications.
